<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-503-587  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 503 587.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 8 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Nihon Sun takes measures against rivals.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Yazawa, Naoyuki.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Nihon Sun Microsystems KK (marketing).andO;Topic:     Computer industryWorkstationsMarket ShareStrategic PlanningDistribution ManagementUNIX.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NIHON SUN TAKES MEASURES AGAINST RIVALS TOKYO, JAPAN, 1990 AUG 20 (NB) --Defending its leading position against other Unix-based WS (workstation)makers, the Japanese subsidiary of U.S.-based Sun Microsystems plans tosolidify its sales channels.andM;Nihon Sun Microsystems is distributing its machines with additional valuesvia general traders, such as C.Ito andamp; Co. and its group firms, and suppliesthem on an OEM (original equipment manufacturing) basis to leadingelectronics makers, such as Toshiba and Fujitsu.andM;To prepare for expected fierce competition among Unix-based WS makers,including Digital Equipment Corp. and NEC which are aiming to acquire 20percent of the market share within few years, the leading player is launchingan Industry Marketing Division.andM;Due to its dependence for sales on other firms, Nihon Sun Microsystems hasonly 15 sales staff members, not enough marketing specialists to support itssales partners.andP;  The new division, however, is expected to hire 30 engineerswithin a year.andM;An opening gambit of the WS firm was the capture of Yoshihiko Komatsu, formerpresident of U.S.-based BBN Communications' Japanese subsidiary, to managethe division.andM;Komatsu reportedly gained experience in WS marketing when he worked forApollo Computer Japan, acquired by Hewlett-Packard last year.andM;(Naoyuki Yazawa/19900816/Press Contact: Nihon Sun Microsystems, 03-221-7228)</TEXT></DOC>